cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses IoT infrastructure and its potential for changing how people interact and live. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper proposes scalable architectures and mechanisms for deploying and managing multiple instances of Semantic Virtual Space (SVS) on top of cloud-enabled IoT infrastructure. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible category as the paper mentions the use of blockchains for increased safety and situation awareness of smart cities. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a potential category as the paper discusses the collaborative processing of streamed data from large numbers of IoT devices for real-time decision making. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper proposes mechanisms for automating the deployment and management of multiple SVS instances.
